The paper discusses the design and implementation of a virtual assistant for software engineering tasks, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves natural language processing and dialogue systems, which are relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves human-computer interaction, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the study involves machine learning and data analysis, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
